history.content: CS 294-43 is just a paper reading seminar - e.g. grad students read papers and every week some students sign up to summarize a paper in a presentation. You can ask if they will allow you to join without CS 280, but I doubt it. But you also aren't missing any curriculum.

The course website says that CS280 is a prerequisite for CS294-43, but I only have one semester left and would like to know whether I can (and able to follow the lecture if I) just take them concurrently.
